By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Tuesday announced that the country has recorded 226 new cases of the Coronavirus across various states of the country with death toll now 192. Announcing via its official Twitter handle on Tuesday night, the Center stated that 131 cases were recorded in Lagos State, 25 cases in Ogun State 15 cases in Plateau State, eleven cases in Edo State, seven cases in Kaduna State and six cases in Oyo State. The tweet further revealed that  five cases each were recorded in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) and Adamawa State, four cases in Jigawa, Ebonyi and Borno State, three cases in Nasarawa State, two cases in Bauchi and Gombe State and one case each in Enugu and Bayelsa State. As at now, 6401 persons have tested positive for COVID-19 in Nigeria with  1734 patients discharged and    192 deaths recorded. See details from NCDC@NCDCgov 226 new cases of #COVID19;131-Lagos25-Ogun15-Plateau11-Edo7-Kaduna6-Oyo5-FCT5-Adamawa4-Jigawa4-Ebonyi4-Borno3-Nasarawa2-Bauchi2-Gombe1-Enugu1-Bayelsa6401 cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 1734Deaths: 192   KANO - Three persons who earlier tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in Kano State have recovered from the disease. The State Ministry of Health disclosed this via its Twitter handle in an early-morning post on Thursday. According to the tweet, the recovered patients have been discharged from the government’s facility… May 7, 2020 In "Health" The Kano State government has confirmed the death of two more patients who tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in the state. The state Ministry of Health announced this in a tweet, saying that was the situation in Kano as of 12:15pm on Monday. This brings the total number of COVID-19… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja - (Sundiata Post) - The Total number of 1320 patients discharged since the the index case in early February, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control said that 28